{"name":"Fake note","permission":{"default":0,"YzA4NmM3ZTkwMjJh":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"trigger","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.5.7","systemVersion":0.89}},"content":"<p>Create a token, set its name to \"Open Note\" (or anything else you want in order to identify it), then set its image to the \"icons/svg/book.svg\" or to any other image you want.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Token[Open Note] @Trigger[click] @JournalEntry[note to open] @ChatMessage[You find a note on the floor]</p>","_id":"Mmbml7E7oa42fPuR"}
{"name":"Preloading neighboring maps","permission":{"default":0,"YzA4NmM3ZTkwMjJh":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"trigger","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.5.7","systemVersion":0.89}},"content":"<p>Preload the scene \"level 2\" when the scene named \"level 1\" is viewed by a player</p>\n<p>@Scene[level 1]&nbsp; @Trigger[preload]@Scene[level 2]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Preload the scenes \"level1\" and \"level 3\" when the scene named \"level 2\" is viewed by a player</p>\n<p>@Scene[level 2]&nbsp; @Trigger[preload]@Scene[level 1]@Scene[level 3]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Preload the scenes \"level 2\" and \"level 4\" when the scene named \"level 3\" is viewed by a player</p>\n<p>@Scene[level 3]&nbsp; @Trigger[preload]@Scene[level 2]@Scene[level 4]</p>","_id":"QBghFwYOAE13OI7B"}
{"_id":"VBosS8tovEZeaSxS","name":"Getting started","permission":{"default":0,"YzA4NmM3ZTkwMjJh":3},"folder":"","flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"trigger","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.5.7","systemVersion":0.89}},"content":"<p>Import the 'Transparent token' actor from the Trigger Happy compendium into your world, then drag and drop it into your scenes, change its name to something unique, then use the examples from the journals compendium and macros from Furnace's and DynamicEffects macro compendiums.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Refer to @Compendium[trigger-happy.journals.vBMZspqIPme7SX7P]{README} for more details and links to step by step instructions and video tutorials.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"name":"Hole in the ground","permission":{"default":0,"YzA4NmM3ZTkwMjJh":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"trigger","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.5.7","systemVersion":0.89}},"content":"<p>This requires LMRTFY module and Furnace enabled, and will request from the player to roll an acrobatics check, if they trigger a trap by moving into or stepping over your trigger token named \"tripwire\". You need to have the \"roll-skill\" macro from Furnace's macro compendium imported into your world.</p>\n<p>@Token[tripwire] @ChatMessage[/roll-skill acr] @Trigger[capture move]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This trigger requires the \"DoTrapAttack\" macro from the DynamicEffects sample macros compendium module, with the modules Dynamic Effects, Furnace and optionally minor-qol enabled.</p>\n<p>It will trigger an attack from the \"Fall damage\" item of the \"Floor\" actor, and will toggle visibility of the token \"Rotting floorboard\".</p>\n<p>@Token[Rotting floorboard] @Trigger[capture move] @ChatMessage[/DoTrapAttack Floor \"Fall damage\" \"Rotting floorboard\"] @ChatMessage[The floor was rotten, and you fall through]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can also create a macro that only calls the DynamicEffects.toggleVisibility API, without making an actual attack. You could also make the trigger teleport the player to the lower level as they fall through the floor.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"j96w4s3GprJQ052K"}
{"name":"Teleporting stairs","permission":{"default":0,"YzA4NmM3ZTkwMjJh":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"trigger","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.5.7","systemVersion":0.89}},"content":"<p>These triggers require the use of the \"TeleportToToken\" macro available in Dynamic Effect's Sample macros compendium, and the Dynamic Effects and Furnace modules enabled.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If a player steps, or crosses the path of the token with the name \"Teleport trigger\", they will be teleported to the same position as the token with the name \"Destination teleport\", which can be in the same scene or any other scene.</p>\n<p>Make sure the destination token has a unique name. You can also adjust the second and third parameters to indicate a relative position to it. Refer to Dynamic Effect's README for more information</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/tposney/dynamiceffects/-/blob/master/Readme.md\">https://gitlab.com/tposney/dynamiceffects/-/blob/master/Readme.md</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>@Token[Teleport trigger] @ChatMessage[/TeleportToToken \"Destination teleport\" 0 0] @Trigger[capture move]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Link the top of stairs in level 1 to the bottom of stairs in level 2.</p>\n<p>When player reached the top of the stairs, they get teleported one grid above the bottom stairs in the level 2, and when they reach the bottom of those stairs, they get teleported one grid below the top stairs in level 1</p>\n<p>@Token[top of stairs level 1] @ChatMessage[/TeleportToToken \"bottom of stairs level 2\" 0 -1] @Trigger[capture move]</p>\n<p>@Token[bottom of stairs level 2] @ChatMessage[/TeleportToToken \"top of stairs level 1\" 0 1] @Trigger[capture move]</p>","_id":"utpT19BwLeEKBE8u"}
{"_id":"vBMZspqIPme7SX7P","name":"README","permission":{"default":0,"YzA4NmM3ZTkwMjJh":3},"folder":"","flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"trigger","system":"dnd5e","coreVersion":"0.5.7","systemVersion":0.89}},"content":"<p>Welcome to Trigger Happy!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Here are step by step instructions :</p>\n<p>1 - Create a folder in your journal directory called \"Trigger Happy\",</p>\n<p>2 - Create a journal entry in that folder</p>\n<p>3 - Create your triggers, one trigger per line, followed by its effects</p>\n<p>4 - Save the entry, and have fun.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A trigger can be :&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- An actor : Any token belonging to that actor will activate the trigger : @<span class=\"ignore\">Actor</span>[name]</p>\n<p>- A token : Any token with the same name as your trigger token will activate the trigger : @Token[name]</p>\n<p>- A scene : Whenever the scene is loaded, the trigger will activate : @<span class=\"ignore\">Scene</span>[scene name]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For ease of use, you can drag &amp; drop triggers and effects into your journal entry.</p>\n<p>The format is :&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- The first element in the trigger line is your trigger activator (Actor, Scene, Token)</p>\n<p>- The rest of the elements on the line are your trigger effects (Actor, Scene, Token, ChatMessage, Macro, RollTable, JournalEntry)</p>\n<p>- Optionally, you can also add trigger options with @Trigger[option]</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For examples, look at the other journal entries in the Trigger Happy Compendium.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For more details on the syntax and options available, please refer to the README from the website :&nbsp;<a href=\"https://github.com/kakaroto/fvtt-module-trigger-happy/blob/master/README.md\">https://github.com/kakaroto/fvtt-module-trigger-happy/blob/master/README.md</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can also refer to this \"Introduction to Trigger Happy\" video tutorial by '<a href=\"https://patreon.com/dndpopulationme\">D&amp;D Population Me</a>' : <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=okTWYO4oEMA\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=okTWYO4oEMA</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;'<a href=\"https://patreon.com/dndpopulationme\">D&amp;D Population Me</a>' has also made two useful step by step guides for the most common use cases for using Trigger Happy :</p>\n<p>- Token teleportation tutorial : <a href=\"https://forums.forge-vtt.com/t/trigger-happy-teleportation-tutorial/2117/6\">https://forums.forge-vtt.com/t/trigger-happy-teleportation-tutorial/2117/6</a></p>\n<p>- Scene Trap tutorial :<a href=\"https://forums.forge-vtt.com/t/trigger-happy-traps/3448/4\"> https://forums.forge-vtt.com/t/trigger-happy-traps/3448/4</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
